---
// Three card section
---

<section id="faq" class="bg-white dark:bg-black border-b dark:border-zinc-800 py-8">
  <div class="container mx-auto flex flex-wrap pt-4 pb-12">
    <h2
      class="w-full my-2 text-5xl font-black leading-tight text-center text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100"
    >
      FAQ
    </h2>
    <div class="w-full mb-4">
      <div
        class="h-1 mx-auto gradient w-64 opacity-25 my-0 py-0 rounded-t"
      ></div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 p-6">
      <div
        class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 shadow rounded-2xl overflow-hidden"
      >
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 md:gap-4 py-6">
          <p class="w-full text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-xs md:text-sm px-6 mt-6 uppercase tracking-wide">
            THE BASICS
          </p>
          <div class="w-full font-bold text-xl text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 px-6">
            What is Nostr?
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-base leading-relaxed px-6 mb-8">
            Nostr is <a href="https://nostr.com/" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">an open protocol</a> with a chance of working. A simple standard that defines a scalable architecture of clients and servers that can be used to spread information freely. Anyone can build on it, and anyone can use it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 p-6">
      <div
        class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 shadow rounded-2xl overflow-hidden"
      >
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 md:gap-4 py-6">
          <p class="w-full text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-xs md:text-sm px-6 mt-6 uppercase tracking-wide">
            THE APP
          </p>
          <div class="w-full font-bold text-xl text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 px-6">
            Why Boris?
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-base leading-relaxed px-6 mb-8">
            Boris is the reading app I always wanted to have. I had <a href="https://dergigi.com/2022/12/18/a-vision-for-a-value-enabled-web/" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">this idea</a> for <a href="https://dergigi.com/2023/04/04/purple-text-orange-highlights/" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">a reading app</a> for a long time, and now I finally sat down and built it. The name comes from <a href="https://relay.dergigi.com/03e174145e1f410772bb8c3e79b153ac0077fe482d7006b1f0ed67a81d475bb9.png" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">a hallucinated answer</a> to the question "Who invented the highlight marker?".
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full md:w-1/3 p-6">
      <div
        class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 shadow rounded-2xl overflow-hidden"
      >
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 md:gap-4 py-6">
          <p class="w-full text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-xs md:text-sm px-6 mt-6 uppercase tracking-wide">
            THE NOSTR WAY
          </p>
          <div class="w-full font-bold text-xl text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 px-6">
            Are my Highlights public?
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-base leading-relaxed px-6 mb-8">
            Yes. All highlights and annotations are public. While nostr supports private bookmarks, highlights and annotations are public by default. Boris adheres to <a href="https://nostrbook.dev/kinds/9802" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">NIP-84</a> and publishes highlights and annotations to your relays.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

